<div class="dcf-wrapper">
  <div class="header">
    <div class="header-content">
      <div class="tag">Original Research</div>
      <h1>Kinder Morgan (KMI)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Kinder Morgan. — derived strictly from historical financials and mathematical relationships.</p>
      <p class="date">Updated March 18, 2026</p>
      <div class="gemini">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
    <div class="verdict-card">
      <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
      <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
      <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice !== null ? currentPrice.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
      <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
        {verdictText}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">${revenueHistory.length > 0 ? (revenueHistory[revenueHistory.length-1].value / 1000000000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Latest Revenue</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">${(baseCashFlow / 1000000000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Operating Cash Flow</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">${epsHistory.length > 0 ? epsHistory[epsHistory.length-1].value.toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
        <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">{marginHistory.length > 0 ? marginHistory[marginHistory.length-1].operating : 'N/A'}%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
    <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
    <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model. All inputs are strictly derived mathematically from current historical data and explicit constants without subjective adjustments.</p>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">1</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Base Cash Flow Adaptation for Midstream</h4>
        <p>Because midstream and pipeline companies like Kinder Morgan operate with consistently high structural Capital Expenditures that often result in volatile or negative standard Free Cash Flow (FCF), we strictly use the actual <strong>Operating Cash Flow (OCF)</strong> as the base proxy for cash generation. The latest OCF is ${Math.round(baseCashFlow / 1000000).toLocaleString()}M.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">2</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Project CF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
        <p>We mathematically project CF growth based on the 5-year historical Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) of the Operating Cash Flow. This calculated rate is <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(2)}%</strong>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">3</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
        <p>After Year 5, we use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>. The terminal growth rate is derived from the 5-year historical revenue CAGR, strictly capped at a 3% GDP proxy. The calculated terminal rate is <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(2)}%</strong>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">4</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Discount to present value</h4>
        <p>All future cash flows are discounted using a rate derived from the explicitly provided 10Y Treasury yield (4.18%) plus a dynamic equity risk premium calculated using the stock's beta ({beta}). The calculated discount rate is <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%</strong>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="method-step">
      <div class="step-num">5</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
        <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${netCash.toLocaleString()}M) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString()}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
    <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
    <p>Every assumption is strictly derived from empirical data.</p>

    <div class="assumption-grid">
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">CF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
        <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(2)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          Mathematically derived from the 5-year Compound Annual Growth Rate of Kinder Morgan's Operating Cash Flow.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC Proxy)</div>
        <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          Strictly derived: 10Y Treasury (4.18%) + (Beta {beta} × standard 5% Equity Risk Premium proxy).
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="assumption-card">
        <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
        <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(2)}%</div>
        <div class="rationale">
          Mathematically derived from the 5-year historical revenue CAGR, strictly capped at 3% to reflect long-term macroeconomic bounds.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
    <h2>Projected Cash Flows (Base: OCF)</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
            <th>CF ($M)</th>
            <th>PV Factor</th>
            <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Base</td>
            <td>${Math.round(baseCashFlow / 1000000).toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>—</td>
          </tr>
          {projectedCF.map(p => (
            <tr>
              <td>Year {p.year}</td>
              <td>${p.cf.toLocaleString()}</td>
              <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
              <td>${p.pvCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
    <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
            <th>Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Year 6 CF</td>
            <td>${Math.round(cfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Terminal Value</td>
            <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
    <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
            <th>Value ($M)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
            <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
            <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>= Enterprise Value</td>
            <td>${enterpriseValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>+ Net Cash (Cash − Debt)</td>
            <td>${netCash.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>= Equity Value</td>
            <td>${equityValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>÷ Shares Outstanding</td>
            <td>{sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="row-total">
            <td>Intrinsic Value Per Share</td>
            <td class="highlight-cell">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ HISTORICAL CHARTS ═══ -->
    <h2>Financial Track Record</h2>
    <p>Historical data sourced via yfinance.</p>

    <h3>Revenue ($B)</h3>
    <div class="bar-chart">
      {revenueHistory.map(r => (
        <div class="bar-row">
          <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
          <div class="bar-track">
            <div class="bar-fill revenue" style={`width: ${r.value > 0 ? (r.value / (revenueHistory[revenueHistory.length-1]?.value || 1)) * 100 : 0}%`}>
              ${(r.value / 1000000000).toFixed(1)}B
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h3>Operating Cash Flow ($B)</h3>
    <div class="bar-chart">
      {ocfHistory.map(r => (
        <div class="bar-row">
          <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
          <div class="bar-track">
            <div class="bar-fill ocf" style={`width: ${r.value > 0 ? (r.value / (ocfHistory[ocfHistory.length-1]?.value || 1)) * 100 : 0}%`}>
              ${(r.value / 1000000000).toFixed(1)}B
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h3>Earnings Per Share (Diluted)</h3>
    <div class="bar-chart">
      {epsHistory.map(r => (
        <div class="bar-row">
          <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
          <div class="bar-track">
            <div class="bar-fill eps" style={`width: ${r.value > 0 ? (r.value / (epsHistory[epsHistory.length-1]?.value || 1)) * 100 : 0}%`}>
              ${r.value.toFixed(2)}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ MARGIN TRENDS ═══ -->
    <h3>Margin Trends</h3>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
            <th>Operating Margin</th>
            <th>Profit Margin</th>
            <th>OCF Margin</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {marginHistory.map(m => (
            <tr>
              <td>{m.year}</td>
              <td>{m.operating}%</td>
              <td>{m.profit}%</td>
              <td>{m.ocfMargin}%</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS ═══ -->
    <h2>Sensitivity Analysis</h2>
    <p>Exploring intrinsic value variations based on discount rate and growth rate permutations.</p>

    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table class="sensitivity-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="text-align:left">Discount Rate ↓ / Growth →</th>
            {sensitivityGrowth.map(g => (
              <th class={Math.abs(g - growthRatePhase1) < 0.0001 ? 'current' : ''}>{(g * 100).toFixed(1)}%</th>
            ))}
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {sensitivityTable.map(row => (
            <tr>
              <td>{(row.dr * 100).toFixed(1)}%</td>
              {row.values.map((v, i) => (
                <td class={Math.abs(row.dr - discountRate) < 0.0001 && Math.abs(sensitivityGrowth[i] - growthRatePhase1) < 0.0001 ? 'current' : ''}>
                  ${v}
                </td>
              ))}
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ WHAT THE MODEL DOESN'T CAPTURE ═══ -->
    <h2>Risks & Limitations</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>CapEx Requirements:</strong> Utilizing Operating Cash Flow inherently bypasses massive capital expenditures required for midstream pipeline maintenance and expansion.</li>
      <li><strong>Regulatory & Environmental:</strong> Pipeline operations face significant regulatory hurdles, environmental litigation, and shifting energy policy risks.</li>
      <li><strong>Interest Rates:</strong> High debt loads (${Math.round(totalDebt).toLocaleString()}M) make KMI sensitive to refinancing rates which may compress future margins.</li>
      <li><strong>Commodity Volume Dependencies:</strong> While contracts are often fee-based, severe shifts in natural gas transport volumes can impact utilization rates.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>Why use Operating Cash Flow instead of Free Cash Flow?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Midstream pipeline companies are highly capital intensive. Their traditional Free Cash Flow (OCF - CapEx) is often negative or extremely volatile due to massive, irregular growth CapEx. Using OCF provides a more stable baseline for evaluating the cash generation of core operations, though it requires acknowledging that sustaining CapEx is omitted from the base rate.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How is the discount rate calculated?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">It is derived strictly mathematically: the explicitly provided 10Y Treasury yield (4.18%) plus the stock's beta ({beta}) multiplied by a standard 5% equity risk premium proxy.</div>
      </details>
    </div>

